    "title": "Unlimited gateway approvals persist and can drain proxy-held tokens even after delisting",
    "locations": [
      "onchain_auto/0x3335a88bb18fd3b6824b59af62b50ce494143333/contracts/RubicProxy.sol:81",
      "onchain_auto/0x3335a88bb18fd3b6824b59af62b50ce494143333/contracts/RubicProxy.sol:91",
      "onchain_auto/0x3335a88bb18fd3b6824b59af62b50ce494143333/rubic-bridge-base/contracts/libraries/SmartApprove.sol:22",
      "onchain_auto/0x3335a88bb18fd3b6824b59af62b50ce494143333/rubic-bridge-base/contracts/libraries/SmartApprove.sol:24",
      "onchain_auto/0x3335a88bb18fd3b6824b59af62b50ce494143333/rubic-bridge-base/contracts/BridgeBase.sol:380"
    ],
    "claim": "`routerCall` gives the caller-chosen `_gateway` a sticky `type(uint256).max` allowance via `SmartApprove`, never revokes it after the route, and only checks the proxy's final token delta. Removing a router from `availableRouters` also does not clear already-granted ERC20 approvals.",
    "impact": "Any currently allowlisted, or formerly allowlisted, gateway/router pair that exposes a public pull/forward primitive can steal current and future balances of the routed token from the proxy, including accumulated Rubic/integrator fees and other users' stranded funds.",
    "paths": [
      "User calls `routerCall` with `_gateway` set to an allowlisted spender/executor.",
      "Proxy executes `approve(_gateway, type(uint256).max)` for the route token.",
      "Gateway or a generic controller later invokes `transferFrom(proxy, attacker, amount)`.",
      "Because approvals are never revoked, the drain remains possible even after `removeAvailableRouter`."
    ]
  },
  {
    "id": "F-002",
    "severity": "High",
