      "onchain_auto/0x3335a88bb18fd3b6824b59af62b50ce494143333/contracts/RubicProxy.sol:91"
    ],
    "claim": "The proxy computes fees and the gateway allowance from `_params.srcInputAmount` instead of the token amount actually received by the contract, then validates only the aggregate post-call balance delta. For deflationary/fee-on-transfer tokens, the gateway can therefore pull more tokens than the user really deposited.",
    "impact": "Previously accumulated balances of the same token held inside the proxy as protocol fees, integrator fees, or stranded funds can be silently consumed to subsidize an attacker's route, enabling repeated reserve drain without privileged access.",
    "paths": [
      "Attacker chooses a taxed/deflationary token that the proxy already holds.",
      "Proxy receives less than `srcInputAmount` on `safeTransferFrom`.",
      "Proxy still approves `_amountIn` derived from the larger nominal amount.",
      "Gateway pulls the shortfall from existing proxy reserves, while the final balance check still passes."
    ]
  },
